other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated measuring up to 13 mm and fluid filled with hyperemia. High-density material within may represent appendicolith. There is surrounding stranding of the fat in the right lower quadrant. Visualized lung bases demonstrate mild atelectasis. The kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically without any hydronephrosis. A 1.4 x 1.3 cm slightly hyperdense lesion within the interpolar region of the left kidney is likely also a hyperdense cyst.
